Class Tree.PushbackStringTokenizer

  • java.lang.Object
    • tree.Tree.PushbackStringTokenizer
  • Enclosing class:
    Tree<V>

    static class Tree.PushbackStringTokenizer
extends java.lang.Object
    A Tokenizer that returns one of four things: a left parenthesis, a right parenthesis, a sequence of non-whitespace, non-parenthesis characters, or null if there are no more tokens.
    Author:
    David Matuszek

      • hasNext

      • next

        java.lang.String next()
        Returns the next token (or a pushed back token, if there is one.) A token may be a left parenthesis, a right parenthesis, or any sequence of other, non-whitespace characters.

        Unlike most tokenizers, this tokenizer will return null if there are no remaining tokens.

        Returns:
        The next token, or null if there are no more.

      • pushBack

        Parameters:
        token - The token to be reused.
